= Veinte años

MÉXICO, D.F., febrero de 1988 —

The campaign is in the plazas: Cárdenas in La Laguna drawing crowds the press declines to count, Castillo working the union halls, Salinas touring a country that has stopped applauding, and in every district office of the Comisión, Bartlett's men preparing July's arithmetic. Twenty years since the plaza of Tlatelolco — and five months from the night the system will have to choose between counting and surviving.

The eve. Twenty years of work — members, casillas, alliances, the list — are about to be weighed on a single July night. The leadership takes stock of what October's orphans bring to the battle.

- @balance: El balance — y a la campaña.

@balance

The inventory is read without adjectives: [? if fuerza_final >= 95 : the Movement arrives strong — a real force with real infrastructure, and the wave rising to meet it. ?][? if fuerza_final >= 60 and fuerza_final < 95 : the Movement arrives standing — enough built to matter, not enough to be safe. ?][? if fuerza_final < 60 : the Movement arrives thin — twenty years distilled into too few hands. The wave may carry others. ?] Five months to the sixth of July.
